		Rule of thumb for ordering class elements
public static final (constants)
public static
public
private
private singleton reference go near the constructor(s).

		Rule of thumb for ordering methods elements
		(Headers shown below are in order of frequency, for easy copy-n-paste.)
Constructors and related methods
public static
public
private
private static --are these needed? 


